The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal/image reconstruction, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Computer Vision (cs.CV), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Poisson noise and the focus on non-negativity and flux preservation constraints suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Signal Processing (cs.SI) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
